This script will install 3rd party tools for Matterhorn.
You should execute it with administrative rights or you
will get errors when libraries will be installed in
/usr/local/bin.

Prerequsites for running this script:
- zlib-devel (zlib1g-dev on Ubuntu)
- c, c++ compiler (gcc, g++ on Ubuntu, gcc, gcc-c++ on RedHat)
- yacc (byacc)
- svn (subversion)
- wget (if it is not installed yet)
- patch (if it is not installed yet)

For building ffmpeg with faad library, you will also need:
- autoconf
- libtool